content.text:
Perfect! I found the issue. The `PersistentWebView.android.tsx` has this code:

```typescript
const isVisible = pathname.includes('/course');

if (!isVisible) {
  console.log('PersistentWebView (Android): Not visible, returning null');
  return null;
}
```

The problem is that `pathname` is changing between `/course` and `/` (the root), causing the WebView to unmount and return `null`. This is exactly what the logs show - it switches between visible and not visible.

The fix is simple: **Remove the visibility check entirely from `PersistentWebView.android.tsx`**. The component should always render when it's mounted by its parent (`course.android.tsx`). The parent component controls when to mount/unmount it, not the WebView itself.

Create a custom Expo config plugin to fix the Material3Expressive theme issue permanently
Create a new file at the project root called plugins/withMaterial3Expressive.js with the following content:
javascriptconst { withAppBuildGradle } = require('@expo/config-plugins');

module.exports = function withMaterial3Expressive(config) {
  return withAppBuildGradle(config, (config) => {
    const buildGradle = config.modResults.contents;

    const materialDep = `implementation("com.google.android.material:material:1.4.0-alpha02")`;

    if (!buildGradle.includes('com.google.android.material:material:1.4.0-alpha02')) {
      config.modResults.contents = buildGradle.replace(
        /dependencies\s*\{/,
        `dependencies {\n    ${materialDep}`
      );
    }

    return config;
  });
};
Then open app.json and add this plugin to the plugins array, as the first item:
json"plugins": [
  "./plugins/withMaterial3Expressive",
  "expo-font",
  "expo-router",
  "expo-web-browser",
  ...rest of plugins
]
The full updated plugins array should look like this:
json"plugins": [
  "./plugins/withMaterial3Expressive",
  "expo-font",
  "expo-router",
  "expo-web-browser",
  [
    "expo-build-properties",
    {
      "android": {
        "compileSdkVersion": 36,
        "targetSdkVersion": 34,
        "minSdkVersion": 24,
        "buildToolsVersion": "34.0.0",
        "enableProguardInReleaseBuilds": false,
        "enableShrinkResourcesInReleaseBuilds": false,
        "usesCleartextTraffic": true
      }
    }
  ],
  [
    "react-native-edge-to-edge",
    {
      "android": {
        "enforceNavigationBarContrast": false
      }
    }
  ]
]
